</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="57.[123,652,193,1360]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
ETYMOLOGY: The trivial name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[515,601,1249,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torosus">
<emphasis box="[515,601,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">torosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Latin adjective meaning bulging. I refer to the robustness of the body conformation of this small beetle.
</paragraph>
